In this activity i will use wireshark to analyze a pcap file with SMTP traffic
To find the smtp response codes i start by filtering the results using smtp.response.code. I found out that this file has 19 220 service ready responses
There's a response that indicates that the email was blocked by spamhaus.org and the response code was 553 with the full code being Requested action not taken: mailbox name not allowed (553)
6 messages were blocked for presenting potential security issues and had 552 as a response code
Now i checked how many smtp packets were available for analysis and they are 512. I analyzed the packet n. 270 and found a attachment named document.zip
The mail was not sent because the the host ip n. 212.253.25.152 did not recieve it. The possible cause could be a network problem
I also filtered by imf for a message containing attachment.src and found out which email client was used: Microsoft Outlook Express 6.00.2600.0000. The encoding used is base64
